 based on its pronunciation in Shanghai dialect, see   Quan   2.","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 曾, see   Zeng  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ren","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Yong, Hong, Hui, Chuan, Gang, Guang, Jian, Liang, Lihua, Ning, Qing, Chang, Min, Shen, Yiming.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 任, a term for women's rank of peerage in ancient Chinese: (i) it is said that the surname can be traced back to one of the 25 sons of the legendary Huang Di, the ‘Yellow Emperor’ (<i>c.</i> 27th century  BC ). (ii) from Ren (任), the name of an ancient state (located in Renxian in Hebei province) granted to Yu Yang, said to be a son or grandson of the legendary Huang Di, the ‘Yellow Emperor’ (<i>c.</i> 27th century  BC ). His descendants adopted the name of the state as their surname. (iii) from Ren (任), the name of a state (located in Shandong province) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","English: variant of   Renn   2."]}]},{"name":"Godefroy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["(2010: NA)","French: from the personal name <i>Godefroy</i>, from ancient Germanic <i>Godafrid</i>, composed of the elements <i>god</i> ‘god’ and <i>frid</i> ‘peace’. This surname is also found in England, where it is of Huguenot origin. Compare   Godfroy  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Godfroy","meanings":["From the Old French name <i>Godefroy</i>, which is of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>god</i> ‘god’ (or <i>gōd</i> ‘good’) + <i>fred</i>, <i>frid</i> ‘peace’. This was adopted by the Normans, and brought to England by immigrants from the Low Countries and France. It was borne by a Norman saint (  <i>c.</i>1066–1115 ) who became bishop of Amiens. There has been considerable confusion with   Geoffrey ."]},{"name":"Goffin","meanings":["Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): metonymic occupational from German <i>Hopfen</i> ‘hops’. The initial <i>g</i> is due to Russian influence, since Russian has no <i>h</i> and alters it to <i>g</i> in borrowed words and names.","French and Walloon: from a pet form of the personal name   Godefroy  .","French and Walloon: possibly also a nickname from a diminutive of Old French <i>goffe</i> ‘heavy, coarse’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Godefroy EN LOUVENCOURT was born in 1042, in Louvencourt, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, his father, Wauthier DE LOUVENCOURT, was 32 and his mother, Louise De Acheux-En-Amiénois, was 21. He had at least 1 daughter with Blanche de Marieux. He died in 1097, in his hometown, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1042–1097":"1042–1097","1037–1106":"1037–1106","–1099":"–1099","1055–1109":"1055–1109","1092–1144":"1092–1144","1010–1067":"1010–1067","1021–1076":"1021–1076","1055":"1055","1099":"1099","1076":"1076","1021":"1021","1010":"1010","1042":"1042","1097":"1097","1092":"1092","1106":"1106","1037":"1037","1067":"1067","1144":"1144","1109":"1109","Louvencourt, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Louvencourt, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Louvencourt, Somme, Picardie, France":"Louvencourt, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Longueval, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Longueval, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1042–1097":"1042–1097","1037–1106":"1037–1106","–1099":"–1099","1055–1109":"1055–1109","1092–1144":"1092–1144","1010–1067":"1010–1067","1021–1076":"1021–1076","1055":"1055","1099":"1099","1076":"1076","1021":"1021","1010":"1010","1042":"1042","1097":"1097","1092":"1092","1106":"1106","1037":"1037","1067":"1067","1144":"1144","1109":"1109","Louvencourt, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Louvencourt, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Ranska","Louvencourt, Somme, Picardie, France":"Louvencourt, Somme, Picardie, Ranska","Longueval, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Longueval, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Ranska"},"fr":{"1042–1097":"1042–1097","1037–1106":"1037–1106","–1099":"–1099","1055–1109":"1055–1109","1092–1144":"1092–1144","1010–1067":"1010–1067","1021–1076":"1021–1076","1055":"10